get submit button "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
=================================================================

NAME
----

get submit button - Returns a submit button, with provided text and appropriate class

SYNOPSIS
--------

Returns a submit button, with provided text and appropriate class

USAGE
-----

` <?php get_submit_button( $text, $type, $name, $wrap, $other_attributes ); ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$text` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) The text of the button (defaults to 'Save Changes')
    Default:

 `$type` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) The type of button. One of: primary, secondary, delete
    Default: primary

 `$name` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) The HTML name of the submit button. Defaults to
    "submit". If no id attribute is given in \$other\_attributes below,
    \$name will be used as the button's id.
    Default: submit

 `$wrap` 
:   ([*boolean*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Boolean "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) True if the output button should be wrapped in a
    paragraph tag, false otherwise. Defaults to true
    Default: true

 `$other_attributes` 
:   ([*array|string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Array.7Cstring "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Other attributes that should be output with the button.
    Defaults to no other attributes.
    Default:

CHANGE LOG
----------

Since: [3.1](/Version_3.1 "Version 3.1")

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`get_submit_button()` is located in `wp-admin/includes/template.php`

